The paper discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) to model high-dimensional data, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper also addresses the challenges of training instability and mode collapse, which are specific issues that arise in GANs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a new metric for evaluating GANs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.GR (Graphics).
